<br>
But how does the damage/delay really work?<br>
<br>
As a 7th level Friar, I'm trying to upgrade my weapon. Here are the NPC choices:<br>
<br>
Staff..............................con.......damage....delay.......cost<br>
Elm Staff.......................yellow........6.7........4.5........32 silver<br>
Elm Runed Staff..............yellow.......10.5.......5.0........44 silver<br>
Elm Quarterstaff..............yellow........4.6.......3.0........32 silver<br>
Elm Shod Quarterstaff......yellow........8.9.......4.2........52 silver<br>
<br>
The Elm quarterstaff and the Elm staff cost the same, and the Elm shod quarterstaff is much more expensive. But I'm totally confused on how the system works.<br>
<br>
Any advice on which staff to get? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub38.ezboard.com/ucorladon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Corladon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(10/22/01 12:39:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=53.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How does damage/delay work in the game</span><hr size=1> Anyone have any insight into this? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub38.ezboard.com/ufraxas.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Fraxas</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Grand Master</span><br>  Posts: 1546<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(10/22/01 12:42:00 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=53.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> staff != quarterstaff</span><hr size=1> I think that staves and quarterstaves are different; you might only be able to do your combat styles with a quarterstaff.<br>
<br>
Maybe. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub38.ezboard.com/ugarouin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Garouin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Monk</span><br>  Posts: 113<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(10/22/01 12:50:28 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=53.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: staff != quarterstaff</span><hr size=1> My tiny bit of information...<br>
<br>
You can tell how well a weapon will do based on the damage delay ratio. Just divide it out like in EQ. The following things effect how mucg damage you do.<br>
<br>
1. Quality.<br>
If you staff is all banged up it will do a tad less. Basically if you have been bashing stuff for a while and your packs are full you'll probably need to repair your weapon.<br>
<br>
2. Material.<br>
I'm not sure what the materials are for staves but metal weapons go bronze, iron, steel, alloy and up. You canhave a sowrd that has the same ratio but is made with a higher material and it will do more damage.<br>
<br>
That's all I know.<br>
<br>
Staves and quarterstaves are both under the staff skill. For some reason the the staves have better ratios than the quarterstaves. I have been told that our level 15 epic quest is a quarterstaff that's actually suspose to be a good one. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub38.ezboard.com/ucorladon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Corladon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(10/23/01 8:06:45 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=53.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How does damage/delay work in the game</span><hr size=1> Well, I went out and got a player made Elm Shod Quarterstaff.  It is yellow to me at 7th level (95% quality), and I'm currently hitting for a max of 28 compared to my green /con player made Rowan Shod Quarterstaff (92% quality) that was hitting for a max of 18.<br>
<br>
Also of interest, my weapon skill went from 200 to 300 when I equiped the staff.  That would partially explain where the extra damage comes from.  I got a 50% increase in weapon skill and I now do 50% more damage.<br>
<br>
But I'm still confused on how the damage works in the game.  Both staves have the same damage and delay, so getting a ratio will not work.  I guess everytime I change to the next wood line, I'll get more weapon skill and hence more damage.<br>
